main: ^It is a bridge that stretches from Samar to Leyte across the San Juanico Strait in the Philippines. Its longest length is a steel girder viaduct built on reinforced concrete piers, and its main span is of an arch-shaped truss design.

c-0: ^It is constructed  during the administration of President Ferdinand Marcos through Japanese Official Development Assistance loans. It has a total length of 2.16 kilometers (1.34 mi)—the second longest bridge spanning a body of seawater in the Philippines.
